          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <who name="Greg Banks">gnb@fastmail.fm</who>
            <bug_when>2010-11-18 18:36:17 EDT</bug_when>
            <thetext>This bug is for implementing serverside support for efficient tracking
of conversations between mailboxes, to support smarter clients which
wish to present a conversation view to users.

Provisionally (design details may change in light of implementation
experience), a conversation is defined as the set of messages connected
by message ids found in the Message-Id, In-Reply-To and References headers,
for a particular user&apos;s mailboxes.

Cyrus will automatically extract conversation tracking information from
newly arrived messages, support replication and reconstruction of
conversation information, and provide new protocol features to support
clients.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
